title: Commandry of Nemerow
data: The Commandry of Nemerow (German: Komturei Nemerow or Komturei Gardow) was a commandry of the Knights Hospitaller in the village of Klein Nemerow in Mecklenburg-Vorpommern. It existed from 1285 until 1648. It was originally centred on Gardow, a now-ruined village near Wokuhl-Dabelow. 53°29′24″N 13°12′53″E﻿ / ﻿53.4899°N 13.2146°E﻿ / 53.4899; 13.2146 This German history article is a stub.
